115.3	Slaughterhouse-Five	Slaughterhouse-Five	Slaughterhouse-Five, or The Children's Crusade: A Duty-Dance with Death (1969) is a satirical novel by Kurt Vonnegut about World War II experiences and journeys through time of a soldier called Billy Pilgrim. Ranked the 18th greatest English novel of the 20th century by Modern Library, it is generally recognized as Vonnegut's most influential and popular work.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/6e/Slaughterhousefive.jpg
